      "rdfs:comment": [
        "DEFINITION: A measurable characteristic.",
        "EXAMPLE: Length, weight, cost, cycle time, defect rate, wheelbase, billing rate.",
        "NOTE: Rule of thumb: use the least specific aspect that serves the intended purpose, increasing specificity only when required (e.g., to distinguish between two magnitudes attached to the same object).",
        "NOTE: Depending on implementation, every aspect should be related to a unit group either directly or through a broader aspect. For example, angle of incidence could be related to the broader concept of angle, which in turn is related to a unit group, or it could be related directly to the unit group without the hierarchical relationship."
      ],
      "rdfs:isDefinedBy": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ontology/gistCore14.1.0"
      },
      "rdfs:label": "Aspect",
      "skos:definition": "A measurable characteristic.",
      "skos:example": "Length, weight, cost, cycle time, defect rate, wheelbase, billing rate.",
      "skos:prefLabel": "Aspect",
      "skos:scopeNote": [
        "Rule of thumb: use the least specific aspect that serves the intended purpose, increasing specificity only when required (e.g., to distinguish between two magnitudes attached to the same object).",
        "Depending on implementation, every aspect should be related to a unit group either directly or through a broader aspect. For example, angle of incidence could be related to the broader concept of angle, which in turn is related to a unit group, or it could be related directly to the unit group without the hierarchical relationship."
      ]
